1. Purpose

HPOGraph is a browser-based tool for Human Phenotype Ontology (HPO)
exploration, phenotype matching, and disease/gene prioritization support.
This software is provided free of charge for research, academic,
educational, and other non-commercial purposes, subject to the terms below.

2. Definitions

"Software" means the HPOGraph source code, documentation, scripts, user
interface files, and related materials included in this repository.

"Research and Non-Commercial Use" means use by individuals, academic
institutions, hospitals, laboratories, public research organizations,
students, educators, or non-profit organizations where the use is not
primarily intended for commercial advantage, paid service delivery, product
development, resale, sublicensing, or revenue generation.

"Commercial Use" means any use of the Software, in whole or in part, by or
for a company, commercial laboratory, paid clinical service provider,
contract research organization, pharmaceutical company, biotechnology
company, software vendor, diagnostic company, consultancy, or any other
for-profit organization, including but not limited to:

  - use in a commercial product or service;
  - use in paid clinical, diagnostic, laboratory, or consulting workflows;
  - integration into commercial software, databases, reports, or platforms;
  - use to provide services to third parties for payment;
  - internal use by a for-profit organization for product development,
    business operations, commercial research, or service delivery;
  - redistribution, hosting, sublicensing, or resale as part of a
    commercial offering.

