6. Third-Party Data and Database Terms

The Software may use, reference, process, or display data derived from
third-party resources, including but not limited to:

  - Human Phenotype Ontology, HPO;
  - phenotype-disease annotation resources;
  - OMIM-linked data or identifiers;
  - HGNC gene metadata;
  - other publicly available biomedical databases.

These third-party resources may be subject to their own licenses, terms of
use, attribution requirements, access restrictions, or commercial-use
restrictions.

This License applies only to the HPOGraph Software created by the
copyright holder. It does not grant any rights to third-party databases,
ontologies, annotations, names, identifiers, or other external resources.

Users are responsible for ensuring that their use of all third-party
resources complies with the applicable third-party licenses and terms.

7. Clinical and Research Disclaimer

The Software is provided for research, education, phenotype exploration,
and decision-support purposes only.

The Software is not a medical device, is not clinically validated as a
standalone diagnostic tool, and must not be used as the sole basis for
diagnosis, treatment, reproductive decision-making, or clinical management.

All results require review and interpretation by qualified healthcare,
clinical genetics, laboratory, or research professionals.

